{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1533,"text":"As a software developer and technologist,"},{"time":4479,"text":"I've worked on a number\nof civic technology projects"},{"time":7126,"text":"over the years."},{"time":8472,"text":"Civic tech is sometimes\nreferred to as tech for good,"},{"time":12118,"text":"using technology to solve\nhumanitarian problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":15763,"text":"This is in 2010 in Uganda,"},{"time":17876,"text":"working on a solution\nthat allowed local populations"},{"time":20616,"text":"to avoid government surveillance\non their mobile phones"},{"time":24099,"text":"for expressing dissent."},{"time":26328,"text":"That same technology was deployed\nlater in North Africa"},{"time":29216,"text":"for similar purposes\nto help activists stay connected"},{"time":32998,"text":"when governments were\ndeliberately shutting off connectivity"},{"time":36149,"text":"as a means of population control."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39336,"text":"But over the years, as I have thought\nabout these technologies"},{"time":42522,"text":"and the things that I work on,"},{"time":44523,"text":"a question kind of nags\nin the back of my mind, which is,"},{"time":47542,"text":"what if we're wrong about\nthe virtues of technology,"},{"time":50267,"text":"and if it sometimes actively hurts"},{"time":52519,"text":"the communities\nthat we're intending to help?"},{"time":55677,"text":"The tech industry around the world\ntends to operate under similar assumptions"},{"time":59456,"text":"that if we build great things,"},{"time":61621,"text":"it will positively affect everyone."},{"time":64035,"text":"Eventually, these innovations\nwill get out and find everyone."},{"time":67904,"text":"But that's not always the case."},{"time":70003,"text":"I like to call this blind championing\nof technology \"trickle-down techonomics,\""},{"time":75784,"text":"to borrow a phrase. (Laughter)"},{"time":78129,"text":"We tend to think that if\nwe design things for the select few,"},{"time":81045,"text":"eventually those technologies\nwill reach everyone,"},{"time":83447,"text":"and that's not always the case."},{"time":85002,"text":"Technology and innovation\nbehaves a lot like wealth and capital."},{"time":90018,"text":"They tend to consolidate\nin the hands of the few,"},{"time":92897,"text":"and sometimes they find their way out\ninto the hands of the many."}]},{"cues":[{"time":96287,"text":"And so most of you aren't tackling\noppressive regimes on the weekends,"},{"time":101488,"text":"so I wanted to think of a few examples\nthat might be a little bit more relatable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":105714,"text":"In the world of wearables\nand smartphones and apps,"},{"time":110066,"text":"there's a big movement\nto track people's personal health"},{"time":113329,"text":"with applications that track\nthe number of calories that you burn"},{"time":116401,"text":"or whether you're sitting too much\nor walking enough."},{"time":121220,"text":"These technologies make patient intake\nin medical facilities much more efficient,"},{"time":127561,"text":"and in turn, these medical facilities"},{"time":131496,"text":"are starting to expect\nthese types of efficiencies."},{"time":134083,"text":"As these digital tools\nfind their way into medical rooms,"},{"time":136883,"text":"and they become digitally ready,"},{"time":138928,"text":"what happens to the digitally invisible?"},{"time":141297,"text":"What does the medical experience look like"},{"time":143321,"text":"for someone who doesn't have\nthe $400 phone or watch"},{"time":146655,"text":"tracking their every movement?"},{"time":148448,"text":"Do they now become a burden\non the medical system?"},{"time":151281,"text":"Is their experience changed?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":154079,"text":"In the world of finance,\nBitcoin and crypto-currencies"},{"time":157341,"text":"are revolutionizing the way\nwe move money around the world,"},{"time":160261,"text":"but the challenge with these technologies"},{"time":162658,"text":"is the barrier to entry\nis incredibly high, right?"},{"time":165247,"text":"You need access to the same\nphones, devices, connectivity,"},{"time":169043,"text":"and even where you don't,\nwhere you can find a proxy agent,"},{"time":172178,"text":"usually they require a certain amount\nof capital to participate."},{"time":177217,"text":"And so the question that I ask myself\nis, what happens to the last community"},{"time":182000,"text":"using paper notes when the rest\nof the world moves to digital currency?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":188260,"text":"Another example from my hometown\nin Philadelphia:"},{"time":191055,"text":"I recently went\nto the public library there,"},{"time":193220,"text":"and they are facing an existential crisis."},{"time":195792,"text":"Public funding is dwindling,"},{"time":197465,"text":"they have to reduce their footprint\nto stay open and stay relevant,"},{"time":202641,"text":"and so one of the ways\nthey're going about this"},{"time":205477,"text":"is digitizing a number of the books\nand moving them to the cloud."},{"time":208770,"text":"This is great for most kids. Right?"},{"time":210745,"text":"You can check out books from home,"},{"time":212598,"text":"you can research on the way\nto school or from school,"},{"time":215147,"text":"but these are really two big assumptions,"},{"time":217339,"text":"that one, you have access at home,"},{"time":219336,"text":"and two, that you have access\nto a mobile phone,"},{"time":221936,"text":"and in Philadelphia, many kids do not."},{"time":224812,"text":"So what does their\neducation experience look like"},{"time":227671,"text":"in the wake of a completely\ncloud-based library,"},{"time":231108,"text":"what used to be considered\nsuch a basic part of education?"},{"time":234567,"text":"How do they stay competitive?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":237566,"text":"A final example from\nacross the world in East Africa:"},{"time":241466,"text":"there's been a huge movement\nto digitize land ownership rights,"},{"time":246782,"text":"for a number of reasons."},{"time":248383,"text":"Migrant communities,\nolder generations dying off,"},{"time":251285,"text":"and ultimately poor record-keeping"},{"time":253925,"text":"have led to conflicts over who owns what."},{"time":257392,"text":"And so there was a big movement\nto put all this information online,"},{"time":261664,"text":"to track all the ownership\nof these plots of land,"},{"time":265424,"text":"put them in the cloud,\nand give them to the communities."},{"time":268119,"text":"But actually, the unintended\nconsequence of this"},{"time":271161,"text":"has been that venture capitalists,\ninvestors, real estate developers,"},{"time":275584,"text":"have swooped in and they've begun\nbuying up these plots of land"},{"time":278647,"text":"right out from under these communities,"},{"time":280564,"text":"because they have access\nto the technologies"},{"time":282700,"text":"and the connectivity\nthat makes that possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286137,"text":"So that's the common thread\nthat connects these examples,"},{"time":289287,"text":"the unintended consequences of the tools\nand the technologies that we make."},{"time":292836,"text":"As engineers, as technologists,"},{"time":295801,"text":"we sometimes prefer\nefficiency over efficacy."},{"time":299360,"text":"We think more about doing things\nthan the outcomes of what we are doing."},{"time":303753,"text":"This needs to change."},{"time":305220,"text":"We have a responsibility to think about\nthe outcomes of the technologies we build,"},{"time":309251,"text":"especially as they increasingly\ncontrol the world in which we live."},{"time":312734,"text":"In the late '90s,"},{"time":314174,"text":"there was a big push for ethics\nin the world of investment and banking."},{"time":318283,"text":"I think in 2014, we're long overdue\nfor a similar movement"},{"time":322091,"text":"in the area of tech and technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":326573,"text":"So, I just encourage you, as you are all\nthinking about the next big thing,"},{"time":330535,"text":"as entrepreneurs, as CEOs,\nas engineers, as makers,"},{"time":335907,"text":"that you think about\nthe unintended consequences"},{"time":339784,"text":"of the things that you're building,"},{"time":341944,"text":"because the real innovation\nis in finding ways to include everyone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345496,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":347168,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}